cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper is about monocular depth estimation using deep learning-based methods, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of adversarial training, which is a popular technique in the field of deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of context-aware and non-local loss functions, which are related to the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper uses a conditional GAN framework, which is a type of neural network architecture, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category.
